description: Phase 0 founder dataset v3: A549 + HepG2 on the same plate via strict checkerboard randomization. Sentinels are allocated per cell line to preserve identifiability; 48h includes ER/mito dose-pair sentinels for Q_s saturation testing. Timepoints are treated as separate charts.

control_design_rules.checkerboard_cell_line_randomization: Cell lines are interleaved across the plate to deconfound spatial gradients from cell identity.
control_design_rules.sentinels_per_cell_line: Sentinel replicates are allocated separately within each cell line subset so nuisance/geometry checks remain interpretable per cell line.
control_design_rules.late_timepoint_dose_pairs: At 48h, ER and mito sentinels use low/mid dose pairs per cell line to compute Q_s and detect saturation/convergence.
control_design_rules.timepoint_as_chart: Analyses must not mix timepoints; boundaries are chart-gated by timepoint health.

notes: Experimental (non-sentinel) assignments are inherited from the original Phase 0 design per cell line/timepoint/operator/day, then randomized across the cell-line-specific checkerboard positions to minimize spatial confounding.
If your imaging/segmentation pipeline is not cell-line-aware, run per-cell-line QC and feature extraction (or at minimum per-cell-line normalization) to avoid extraction artifacts.
